Quick facts
Founded: 1969 (National League expansion)
Current uniform colors: Dark blue, Sand, and White
Logo design: White interlocking 'S' and 'D'
Hometown Hero: Tony Gwynn
Nicknames: The Friars, the &quot;Pads&quot; (pronounced as &quot;Pods&quot;)
Most winning season: (1998) 98&lt;U+2013&gt;64. Western Division Title and National League Pennant Winners.
Most losing season: (1969) 52&lt;U+2013&gt;110
Local television: Channel 4 San Diego (4SD) (Cable TV only; not available over the air.)
TV announcers: Dick Enberg, Mark Grant, Tony Gwynn (occasionally), Mark Neely (substitute).
